    • Uses of HasInvariant in abstracts

      Subinterfaces of HasInvariant in abstracts 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  UnboundedStorageSpecification<T>
      A FIFO bounded queue of integers with a maximum number of elements that must be at least 1.
      Classes in abstracts that implement HasInvariant 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AbstractQueue<T>
      This class is an abstraction of UnboundedStorageSpecification
      It implements all basic methods of a queue
      As project's requirement, the queue is built by 2 stacks.
      class  AbstractQueueIntPair<T>
      This is an implementation of UnboundedStorageSpecification
      This class implements the basic methods of a queue that has 2 queues and processes with Pairs elements

    • Uses of HasInvariant in models

      Classes in models that implement HasInvariant 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  QueueIntPairSimulation
      This class implements a simulation to calculate the reliable probability of QueueShareStackIntPair by calling push(), pop() and head() randomly
      class  ReliableStack<T>
      This class is an implementation of UnboundedStorageSpecification
      It implements a stack without making an exception condition
      class  UnreliableStack<T>
      This class is an extension of ReliableStack
      It overrides push(), pop() and head() and adds the exception condition to make Stack to be unreliable

    • Uses of HasInvariant in models.design.project

      Classes in models.design.project that implement HasInvariant 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  QueueShareStack<T>
      This class is an extension of AbstractQueue and an implementation of UnboundedStorageSpecification
      In this design, stackIn is a composition meanwhile stackOut(temporary) is aggregation
      This implementation follows the requirement: the stackOut is shared among two queues and play a role as temporary stack
      The tested instances of shared stack may be UnreliableStack or ReliableStack
      class  QueueShareStackIntPair<T>
      This class implements a queue that works with Pairs elements
      It is an extension of AbstractQueueIntPair and an implementation of UnboundedStorageSpecification
      As project's requirement, QueueShareStackIntPair has two QueueShareStack queues
      Two these queues are aggregations of this class.

    • Uses of HasInvariant in models.design.propose

      Classes in models.design.propose that implement HasInvariant 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  Queue2Stack<T>
      This class is an extension of AbstractQueue and an implementation of UnboundedStorageSpecification
      In this design, stackIn and stackOut are two aggregations of this queue
      One of two is not be shared comparing with the design 1
      The tested instances of two stacks may be UnreliableStack or ReliableStack
      class  Queue2StackIntPair<T>
      This class implements a queue that works with Pairs of Integer elements
      It is an extension of AbstractQueueIntPair and an implementation of UnboundedStorageSpecification
      This design implements a queue having 2 Queue2Stack queues
      In this design, two queues are aggregations and they do not share their stacks with the other
      The tested instance of two queues may be built by 4 UnreliableStack or ReliableStack
